#So we canâ€™t subset it like a matrix until you extract one matrix from the list.


# It is totally standard in R when working with lists of matrices â€” the first set of brackets [[...]] pulls the matrix out of the list, and the second set [...] is used to subset that matrix.
#[[1]] is grabbing the actual matrix (genes Ã— samples) for the first group.
